OL,7,FBreaking down in tears, she read her
OL,8,Fstatement in which she questioned how
OL,9,Finsurance companies allowed the events
OL,10,Fto take place for a "quick thrill".
OL,12,FShe said her son had completed the
OL,13,Fdissertation for his degree in
OL,14,Ffootball management days before his
OL,15,Fdeath and was awarded a 2:1
OL,16,Fposthumously.
OL,18,FShe added: "One reckless act has left
OL,19,Four family with a life sentence of
OL,20,Fpain that grows deeper every day."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
