OL,5,Cmeet
OL,7,FThe court heard Hodgson drove "like an
OL,8,Fidiot" on the motorway to get to the
OL,9,Fsecond location and once there drove
OL,10,Fcircuits of the area.
OL,12,FMr Becker said Jack Stocks was
OL,13,Fpersuaded by friends to be a passenger
OL,14,Fin Hodgson's car.
OL,16,FMr Becker said: "They were in the car
OL,17,Fabout 15 minutes. At least once during
OL,18,Fthe laps Jack Stocks looked over at
OL,19,Fthe speedometer and it was in the
OL,20,Fregion of about 100mph."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
