OL,4,CEngland Schoolboys footballer at car
OL,5,Cmeet
OL,7,FThe court heard Hodgson would stop the
OL,8,Fcar when he reached a "strip", where
OL,9,Fsomeone would hold up a green light to
OL,10,Findicate when there was a gap and he
OL,11,Fwould drive at high speeds.
OL,13,FHe was driving down the strip, which
OL,14,Fhad a speed limit of 30mph, when Mr
OL,15,FHarding stepped into the road.
OL,17,FHe sounded his horn and swerved but
OL,18,Fwas unable to avoid him, the court
OL,19,Fheard.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
